  "body": "\n### Description\n\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n*Type*: Bug\n*Summary*: it is possible  to change recipient \\ asset in the wallet with after you fill up all data and tap on \"Sign transaction\". IMO it is better to lock these details after user tap on \"Sign transaction\" and unlock in case when user tap on \"Cancel\"\n\n#### Expected behavior\ncan't change asset / recipient after step 5\n\n\n#### Actual behavior\n![img_30c87091fe57-1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/53793784-d66ca280-3f2e-11e9-8298-0a8e25cb2b41.jpeg)\n\n### Reproduction\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\n\n1) Open Status\n2) Go to wallet\n3) Tap on \"Send Transaction\"\n4) Enter recipient, address, amount\n5) Tap on sign\n6) Change recipient or asset. On large scrrens also possible to change amount.\n\n### Additional Information\n\n* Status version: nightly 05/03/2019; release 0.10.0\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
